1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 15-10 and a new chapter to
2 title 50 of the North Dakota Century Code, relating to the acceptance of health care sharing
3 ministries by an institution of higher education and health care sharing ministries' exemptions
4 from insurance laws and regulations.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
6 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 15-10 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
7 and enacted as follows:
8 Institutions of higher education - Acceptance of health care sharing ministries as
9 health care coverage.
10 1. A student's active participation in a health care sharing ministry, as defined under
11 section 2 of this Act, satisfies any requirement that a student enrolled in an institution
12 of higher education maintain health care coverage, except as provided in
13 subsection 2 .
14 2. Notwithstanding subsection 1, this section does not apply to an international studen t
15 who is required to maintain health insurance coverage in compliance with federal visa
16 regulations, including students holding J, F, or M visas. Institutions of higher education
17 shall require these students to obtain a health insurance policy that meets the
18 minimum standards provided by the United States department of state and a state
19 board of higher education policy governing health insurance requirements for
20 international students.
21 SECTION 2. A new chapter to title 50 of the North Dakota Century Code is created and
22 enacted as follows:
